review:
A journey of trust, faith and care

Dr. Sheetal is an epitome of love and affection. Me and my husband visited her for pre-conception counselling and in the very first meet we were so much impressed and overwhelmed with the way she discussed each and every issue. Then began my beautiful journey of pregnancy. I firmly believe that pregnancy is the most sensitive, emotional and memorable phase for would be parents. Dr. Sheetal is not just my doctor but my friend, guardian and has been by my side throughout. It is always a pleasure to meet her and I was super excited for every meet to come. Being a very knowledgeable doctor, she takes utmost care of her patients and advise whatever is in the best interest for the patient. I always felt am in the safest hands and she was my support system throughout. 

Now, I am a proud mother of a beautiful angel. I have the highest regards for mam and recommend her to every expecting parent for a pregnancy journey so smooth and full of happiness...

review:
** ******* ** *** **** ***** * **** *** ** ***** ** ****** I have been suffering from vaginal white discharge and liquid discharge for long. Visited many gynae but they all disappointed me. Dr Sheetal in the very first meeting said, she will give me medicine for only one week and if doe not help, I should consult a dermatologist. 

She recommended some test as well. But clearly told me that Blood Suga is the only must one. 

Her medicines gave me relief in a week. And her pleasing personality, approachable nature and good temper adds to all her knowledge and experience. 

If anyone in Delhi NCR is looking for a good Gyanecologist, Dr Sheetal Sachdeva is the one you must consult.

Thank you Mam.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
Traumatic birth experience.
I started seeing Dr. Sheetal based on practo stories. I visited her for entire pregnancy many times. Not even once i could find anything that is mentioned by people in their stories. She gets easily offended by questions. There is no personal touch by the way. She never seem bothered by my anxiety. Every body and every pregnancy is different. She literally scolded me and my husband on call when I was in labour and pressurized us to take a decision in few minutes. At that moment in hospital during labour I felt how unlucky I am to have a doctor so rude. I was traumatized after my cesarean 
now after 2 months i have got enough stability to think about what happened to me.
While Reading other stories i felt..did i pay less or what? I don't know where was her friendliness and approachable nature in my case. She never explained me the procedure i might go through so that i can take an informed decision. Upon asking she scolded "make a decision first"
On my latest appointment where i asked her whether i can clean my pubic hair above the stitches. She said yes. I confirmed whether i can use hair removal creams...she got irritated and said...i am not going to discuss this now..i said you can remove so do whatever you like.
I think during my journey i kept on hoping that may be she is good based on practo stories and i should keep patience...today i regret that. I shouldn't have waited.
I wish i had a doctor who understands that for a doctor, delivering a baby is an every day task..but for a patient...it's life changing.
reply_text: Wishing you a better experience with a better dr in future
